  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 3: Regression Model with Feature Engineering\n",
    "\n",
    "Techniques applied (chosen based on the EDA above):\n",
    "\n",
    "| Technique | Applied to | Why |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| Domain feature creation | `HouseAge`, `RemodAge`, `TotalSF`, `TotalBath`, `TotalPorchSF`, `HasPool`, `HasFireplace`, `HasGarage`, `IsRemodeled` | Raw year/area columns are less informative than derived \"age\" and \"total\" measures a buyer actually reasons about |\n",
    "| Interaction features | `Qual_x_TotalSF`, `Qual_x_GrLivArea` | Quality and size interact \u2014 a large *and* high-quality home is worth disproportionately more than the sum of its parts |\n",
    "| Ordinal encoding | `ExterQual`, `KitchenQual` | These categories have a natural order (Ex > Gd > TA > Fa); one-hot encoding would discard that order, ordinal encoding preserves it |\n",
    "| Log transform (skew correction) | `LotArea` (skew 1.47) | Skewed numeric inputs distort linear-model coefficients; only columns with |skew| > 0.75 were transformed |\n",
    "| Log transform (target) | `SalePrice` \u2192 `SalePrice_log` | Matches the right-skewed shape seen in Part 1, stabilizing variance of residuals |\n",
    "| Feature scaling | All numeric features | Standardization (`StandardScaler`) puts features on comparable scales, which matters for regularized/linear models |\n",
    "| One-hot encoding | Remaining nominal categoricals (`Neighborhood`, `HouseStyle`, `GarageType`, `CentralAir`) | No inherent order, so one-hot is appropriate |\n",
    "\n",
    "We deliberately keep the **same algorithm (Linear Regression)** as the baseline so the comparison isolates the effect of feature engineering rather than mixing in the effect of switching models. A separate algorithm comparison is done in the Bonus section."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "output_type": "execute_result",
     "execution_count": 13,
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "   Id  LotArea  OverallQual  ...  Qual_x_GrLivArea  ExterQual_enc  KitchenQual_enc\n",
       "0   1     7440           10  ...             13860              4                2\n",
       "1   2     7433            8  ...             14072              2                3\n",
       "2   3     9865            8  ...             10920              2                2\n",
       "3   4     4165            1  ...               413              1                2\n",
       "4   5     4491           10  ...             21250              2                3\n",
       "\n",
       "[5 rows x 42 columns]"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {}
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fe_df = df.copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Domain feature creation\n",
    "fe_df['HouseAge'] = 2023 - fe_df['YearBuilt']\n",
    "fe_df['RemodAge'] = 2023 - fe_df['YearRemodAdd']\n",
    "fe_df['TotalSF'] = fe_df['TotalBsmtSF'] + fe_df['1stFlrSF'] + fe_df['2ndFlrSF']\n",
    "fe_df['TotalBath'] = fe_df['FullBath'] + 0.5 * fe_df['HalfBath']\n",
    "fe_df['TotalPorchSF'] = fe_df['WoodDeckSF'] + fe_df['OpenPorchSF']\n",
    "fe_df['HasPool'] = (fe_df['PoolArea'] > 0).astype(int)\n",
    "fe_df['HasFireplace'] = (fe_df['Fireplaces'] > 0).astype(int)\n",
    "fe_df['HasGarage'] = (fe_df['GarageCars'] > 0).astype(int)\n",
    "fe_df['IsRemodeled'] = (fe_df['YearBuilt'] != fe_df['YearRemodAdd']).astype(int)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Interaction features\n",
    "fe_df['Qual_x_TotalSF'] = fe_df['OverallQual'] * fe_df['TotalSF']\n",
    "fe_df['Qual_x_GrLivArea'] = fe_df['OverallQual'] * fe_df['GrLivArea']\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ordinal encode quality-scale categoricals\n",
    "qual_map = {'Ex': 4, 'Gd': 3, 'TA': 2, 'Fa': 1}\n",
    "fe_df['ExterQual_enc'] = fe_df['ExterQual'].map(qual_map)\n",
    "fe_df['KitchenQual_enc'] = fe_df['KitchenQual'].map(qual_map)\n",
    "\n",
    "fe_df.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "output_type": "stream",
     "name": "stdout",
     "text": [
      "Skewness before transform:\n",
      " LotArea        1.466414\n",
      "TotalSF        0.124089\n",
      "GrLivArea      0.215479\n",
      "TotalBsmtSF    0.071614\n",
      "1stFlrSF       0.104893\n",
      "dtype: float64\n",
      "\n",
      "Columns log-transformed: ['LotArea']\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Handle skewed numeric distributions with log1p (only where |skew| > 0.75)\n",
    "skewed_candidates = ['LotArea', 'TotalSF', 'GrLivArea', 'TotalBsmtSF', '1stFlrSF']\n",
    "skewness = fe_df[skewed_candidates].skew()\n",
    "print(\"Skewness before transform:\\n\", skewness)\n",
